Given Ip address is : 192.168.40.0
number of subnets =2 (number of host devices)

formula: 2^n= number of subnets=====2^n=2 [n=1] [1 is the number of borrowed bits]

N= 1
subnet mask = 255.255.255.255
11111111.11111111.11111111.10000000 //on the lasat octet 1 is the borrowd bit so rest of the bits are zero
255.255.255.128 [a subnet mask that hands on 128 represent the block size of 128]
------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------
1st subnet:
subnet mask: 255.255.255.128
network id: 192.168.40.0
range of valid host : 192.168.40.1-192.168.40.126
Brodcast id : 192.168.40.127

2nd subnet:
subnet mask: 255.255.255.128
network id:192.168.40.128
range of valid host: 192.168.40.129-192.168.40.254
brodcast id: 192.168.40.255


